{"_id":"Fruityricesalad","preptime":"15","servings":"4","keywords":["diet@vegetarian","cook method.hob, oven, grill@hob","diet@corn-free","occasion@entertaining","special collections@lunchbox","diet@egg-free","diet@cow dairy-free","occasion@prepare-ahead entertaining","diet@wheat-free","diet@peanut-free","diet@dairy-free","meal type@salads","occasion@buffet party","diet@shellfish-free","occasion@picnic","occasion@barbecue","diet@vegan","convenience@add pasta for a complete meal","scalability@good for numbers","diet@demi-veg","main ingredient@rice, potatoes, grains, couscous","diet@gluten-free"],"subtitle":"This nutritious salad can be served hot or cold and is ideal for a buffet or barbecue.","totaltime":"30","cooktime":"15","ingredients":[{"ingredient":"apple juice","measure":"450 ml"},{"ingredient":"water","measure":"450 ml"},{"ingredient":"red pepper","measure":"1"},{"ingredient":"orange","measure":"1"},{"ingredient":"salad onions","measure":"[sup]1[/sup]/[sub]2[/sub] bunch"},{"ingredient":"seedless raisins","measure":"50 g"},{"ingredient":"fresh parsley","measure":"3 tsp"},{"ingredient":"black pepper","measure":"1 dash"},{"ingredient":"white wine vinegar","measure":"6 tsp"},{"ingredient":null,"measure":""},{"ingredient":"olive oil","measure":"300 ml"},{"ingredient":"wholegrain mustard","measure":"2 tsp"},{"ingredient":"long grain brown rice","measure":"225 g"}],"method":[{"step":"1","text":"Put the rice in a pan with the apple juice and water. Bring to the boil. Reduce heat, cover and simmer for 15-20 min or until rice is just tender and the liquid has been absorbed into the rice. "},{"step":"2","text":"Stir in the red pepper, orange, onions and raisins. Mix well. "},{"step":"3","text":"Place all the dressing ingredients into a screw-top jar. Shake together well. Pour over the rice salad. Toss well. "},{"step":"4","text":"Serve either hot or cold. "}],"title":"Fruity rice salad"}